Pantheon Oversight Layer

Each daemon enforces a specific invariant.

Pantheon Module	Role in IWDS
Spider	maintains world graph and object relationships
Mirror	checks invariants and logical consistency
Hound	detects anomalies or physics violations
Dragonfly	manages camera perspective and exploratory generation
Sisyphus	governs simulation time and iteration cycles
Mother Duck	logs every event to the world ledger

Together they ensure the simulation remains stable.

⸻

World State Dataflow

Inside the runtime the world is stored as a scene graph + event ledger.

Scene Graph
    │
    ├── Entities
    │       ├─ terrain
    │       ├─ structures
    │       ├─ characters
    │       └─ objects
    │
    └── Relationships
            ├─ spatial hierarchy
            ├─ navigation links
            └─ interaction affordances

All modifications are appended to the Mother Duck ledger:

Event Ledger
    │
    ├─ timestamp
    ├─ command origin
    ├─ world delta
    ├─ object UUID
    └─ checksum

This enables:
	•	replay
	•	undo
	•	branching timelines
	•	audit trails

⸻

Fidelity Tier System

To maintain performance, the system distributes compute according to attention.

Tier 1 — Far Field
symbolic geometry
low compute cost

Tier 2 — Interactive Region
full spatial runtime objects
physics and navigation active

Tier 3 — Focus Area
neural high-detail rendering
cinematic fidelity

Dragonfly dynamically shifts objects between tiers.

